      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Critics of high-density zoning often raise concerns about increased density being incompatible with long-term resident retention, as it can lead to gentrification and displacement of existing residents and small businesses. They also argue that high-density developments can result in lost parking, reduced property values, and an increased burden on urban infrastructure. Furthermore, critics often point to the potential for increased urban heat islands, noise pollution, and decreased air quality, which can have negative impacts on public health.",
